00:00:00,075 --> 00:00:06,100
Incorporating async and await in JavaScript functions handles asynchronous tasks with ease

2
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:08,838
They provide a cleaner way to work with promises

3
00:00:09,213 --> 00:00:11,938
making asynchronous code appear synchronous

4
00:00:12,325 --> 00:00:14,787
By using async keyword before a function

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,688
it always returns a promise

6
00:00:17,087 --> 00:00:22,113
The await keyword within the function pauses its execution until the promise settles

7
00:00:22,525 --> 00:00:26,488
yielding more readable and manageable asynchronous operations

